scoringPlays.text: Darius Victor 1 Yd Run (Sam Hurwitz Kick)

article.description: Darius Victor punched in a touchdown, Sam Hurwitz kicked four field goals and Towson cruised to a 19-0 win over Delaware on Saturday.
article.headline: Towson shuts down Delaware 19-0
article.story: TOWSON, Md. -- Darius Victor punched in a touchdown, Sam Hurwitz kicked four field goals and Towson cruised to a 19-0 win over Delaware on Saturday. Connor Frazier was 25 of 34 for 284 yards passing as Towson (5-3, 3-2 Colonial) got its first shutout victory since 2005. Christian Summers had 133 yards on eight catches and Marquel Dickerson had 102 yards rushing on 20 carries. The Tigers dominated Delaware (3-5, 2-3), piling up 410 total offensive yards while holding the Blue Hens to just 14 yards passing and 88 on the ground with six first downs. Victor's touchdown run late in the second quarter capped a 10-play, 83-yard drive that included 21- and 37-yard catches by Summers. Hurwitz hit two 39-yard field goals as well as 27- and 34-yard field goals. Delaware's Joe Walker completed just three of his nine passes for 14 yards and an interception.
